---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Why My Websites Are Different | Jake Fixes Tech"
  description="See why Jake Fixes Tech builds faster, safer, and more accessible websites than traditional web agencies — at a fraction of the ongoing cost."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section style="position:relative;overflow:hidden;background-color:rgb(30,64,175);">
    <img src="/hero.jpg" alt="Professional tech workspace with dual monitors" width="1920" height="1080" fetchpriority="high" style="position:absolute;inset:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;z-index:0;" />
    <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(30,64,175,0.88),rgba(37,99,235,0.88));z-index:1;"></div>
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;padding:5rem 1.5rem 4rem 1.5rem;text-align:center;position:relative;z-index:2;">
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#93c5fd;">The Jake Fixes Tech Difference</p>
      <h1 style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;color:white;margin-top:0.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">Why my Websites Are Different</h1>
      <p style="color:#bfdbfe;font-size:1.1rem;line-height:1.75;max-width:42rem;margin:0 auto;">
        A lot has changed in web development over the last decade. Not every agency got the memo.
        Here's an honest look at what separates a modern website from an outdated one — and why it matters for your business.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <section style="background:white;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <h2 style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-bottom:1rem;">Let's be real for a second.</h2>
      <p style="color:#4b5563;line-height:1.85;font-size:1.05rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">
        A lot of web agencies are still building websites the same way they did 10-15 years ago. WordPress themes, bloated plugins, slow load times, and a monthly invoice for things that have been free for years. Meanwhile your business is paying the price — in slow load times, bad Google rankings, security vulnerabilities, and customers who bounce before your page even finishes loading.
      </p>
      <p style="color:#4b5563;line-height:1.85;font-size:1.05rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">
        I build websites differently. Not because I'm trying to be fancy — because the tools available today are genuinely better, faster, and more secure than what most agencies are still using. And I pass those benefits directly to you.
      </p>
      <p style="color:#4b5563;line-height:1.85;font-size:1.05rem;">
        Here's exactly what I mean.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Speed Section -->
  <section style="background:#f8fafc;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:72rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">Performance</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">Speed Isn't a Luxury — It's Everything</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;max-width:36rem;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;line-height:1.75;">Google uses page speed as a ranking factor. Slow sites rank lower, lose visitors, and lose sales. Here's how the numbers stack up.</p>
      </div>

      <div id="speed-grid">
        <div class="speed-card">
          <div class="speed-label">Typical Agency Site</div>
          <div class="speed-bar-wrap">
            <div class="speed-bar speed-bar-bad" style="width:85%;">
              <span>5–15 seconds</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="speed-note">WordPress with plugins, unoptimized images, shared hosting</p>
        </div>
        <div class="speed-card">
          <div class="speed-label">Jake Fixes Tech Site</div>
          <div class="speed-bar-wrap">
            <div class="speed-bar speed-bar-good" style="width:8%;">
              <span style="color:#14532d;margin-left:0.5rem;">0.3s</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="speed-note">Astro static HTML, Cloudflare global CDN, zero unnecessary JavaScript</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="stat-cards">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-number" style="color:#1d4ed8;">93x</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Smaller Page Size</div>
          <div class="stat-sub">125kb vs 11,000kb+</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-number" style="color:#1d4ed8;">50x</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Faster Load Time</div>
          <div class="stat-sub">0.3s vs 15s+</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-number" style="color:#15803d;">100/100</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Lighthouse Performance</div>
          <div class="stat-sub">Every page, every time</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-number" style="color:#15803d;">10/10</div>
          <div class="stat-label">WAVE Accessibility</div>
          <div class="stat-sub">Every single page</div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What is Lighthouse / WAVE -->
  <section style="background:white;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:72rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">The Score That Matters</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">Google Grades Every Website. Here's How to Read the Report Card.</h2>
      </div>
      <div id="tools-grid">
        <div class="tool-card">
          <div class="tool-icon">🔦</div>
          <h3>Google Lighthouse</h3>
          <p>Google's own free tool that grades any website across Performance, Accessibility, Best Practices and SEO — each scored out of 100. Most professional agency sites score 50–75 on performance. Every site I build scores 100/100 on Performance, Best Practices, and SEO on Google's own test.</p>
          <div class="score-box">
            <div class="score-agency">TYPICAL AGENCY: 50–75 Performance</div>
            <div class="score-jake">JAKE FIXES TECH: 100 Performance ✅</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-card">
          <div class="tool-icon">♿</div>
          <h3>WAVE Accessibility Checker</h3>
          <p>WAVE is the industry standard tool that checks whether a website is usable by people with disabilities — including screen reader users, keyboard-only users, and people with visual impairments. Most agency sites have never been checked. Every page I build scores 10/10.</p>
          <div class="score-box">
            <div class="score-agency">TYPICAL AGENCY: Never checked</div>
            <div class="score-jake">JAKE FIXES TECH: 10 / 10 ✅</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-card">
          <div class="tool-icon">⚖️</div>
          <h3>ADA Compliance</h3>
          <p>Under the Americans with Disabilities Act, businesses can be sued for having inaccessible websites. It happens to small businesses regularly. Every site I build meets WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility standards out of the box — no extra charge, no add-on, just built in from day one.</p>
          <div class="score-box">
            <div class="score-agency">TYPICAL AGENCY: Rarely addressed</div>
            <div class="score-jake">JAKE FIXES TECH: WCAG 2.1 AA ✅</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Accessibility Overlay Widget Section -->
  <section style="background:#f8fafc;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">A Common Misconception</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">Those Little Accessibility Widgets Aren't the Answer</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;max-width:40rem;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;line-height:1.75;">You've probably seen them — a small wheelchair icon in the corner of a website that opens a panel to adjust fonts, contrast, and other settings. It's a well-intentioned idea. But it comes with a real problem that's worth understanding.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="widget-compare-grid">
        <div style="background:white;border:2px solid #fca5a5;border-radius:0.75rem;padding:1.5rem;">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">
            <span style="font-size:1.5rem;">⚠️</span>
            <h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;color:#991b1b;margin:0;">Accessibility Overlay Widgets</h3>
          </div>
          <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.625rem;">
            <li style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#374151;">❌ Layered on top of broken underlying code</li>
            <li style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#374151;">❌ Puts the burden on the visitor to fix it themselves</li>
            <li style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#374151;">❌ Can interfere with real screen readers</li>
            <li style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#374151;">❌ Often costs $500–$1,500/year</li>
            <li style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#374151;">❌ Doesn't guarantee ADA compliance</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div style="background:white;border:2px solid #86efac;border-radius:0.75rem;padding:1.5rem;">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">
            <span style="font-size:1.5rem;">✅</span>
            <h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;color:#166534;margin:0;">Built-In Accessibility (My Approach)</h3>
          </div>
          <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.625rem;">
            <li style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#374151;">✅ Proper semantic HTML from the ground up</li>
            <li style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#374151;">✅ Works for every visitor without any extra steps</li>
            <li style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#374151;">✅ Compatible with all screen readers and assistive tools</li>
            <li style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#374151;">✅ Included in every build at no extra charge</li>
            <li style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#374151;">✅ Genuine WCAG AA compliance, verified on every page</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="background:white;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:0.75rem;padding:1.5rem;">
        <p style="color:#4b5563;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.85;margin:0;">
          Think of it this way: a widget that lets a visitor adjust font sizes is a bit like putting the accessible entrance around the back and hoping people find the sign. The intention is good — but the experience isn't. Real accessibility means every visitor arrives to a site that already works for them, no adjustments needed. That's what I build — verified with <strong>WAVE accessibility testing on every single page</strong>, and backed by thorough manual testing on top of that. Automated tools catch a lot, but manual testing catches the rest.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Hidden Costs Section -->
  <section style="background:white;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:72rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">The Real Cost of a Website</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">Stop Paying for Things That Are Free</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;max-width:40rem;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;line-height:1.75;">
          SSL certificates, hosting, backups, CDN protection — these things have been free for years. Some agencies are still charging hundreds of dollars a year for them. Here's the truth.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="compare-cards">

        <div class="compare-header-row">
          <div style="flex:1;min-width:0;"></div>
          <div class="compare-cols">
            <div style="width:220px;text-align:center;font-size:0.8rem;font-weight:700;color:white;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;padding:0 1rem;border-right:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2);">Old School Agency</div>
            <div style="width:220px;text-align:center;font-size:0.8rem;font-weight:700;color:white;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;padding:0 1rem;">Jake Fixes Tech</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="compare-card">
          <div class="compare-feature">
            <div class="feature-name">SSL Certificate</div>
            <div class="feature-desc">The padlock icon that makes your site secure</div>
          </div>
          <div class="compare-cols">
            <div class="compare-agency">$50–$700/yr</div>
            <div class="compare-jake">✅ Free (Cloudflare)</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="compare-card row-alt">
          <div class="compare-feature">
            <div class="feature-name">Website Hosting</div>
            <div class="feature-desc">Where your website lives on the internet</div>
          </div>
          <div class="compare-cols">
            <div class="compare-agency">$30–$100/mo</div>
            <div class="compare-jake">✅ Free (Cloudflare Pages)</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="compare-card">
          <div class="compare-feature">
            <div class="feature-name">Website Backups</div>
            <div class="feature-desc">Saving copies in case something goes wrong</div>
          </div>
          <div class="compare-cols">
            <div class="compare-agency">$20–$50/mo</div>
            <div class="compare-jake">✅ Free (GitHub)</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="compare-card row-alt">
          <div class="compare-feature">
            <div class="feature-name">CDN &amp; DDoS Protection</div>
            <div class="feature-desc">Global speed boost and attack protection</div>
          </div>
          <div class="compare-cols">
            <div class="compare-agency">$20–$200/mo</div>
            <div class="compare-jake">✅ Free (Cloudflare)</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="compare-card">
          <div class="compare-feature">
            <div class="feature-name">Platform</div>
            <div class="feature-desc">What the website is built on</div>
          </div>
          <div class="compare-cols">
            <div class="compare-agency">WordPress (outdated, hack-prone)</div>
            <div class="compare-jake">✅ Astro (modern, static, secure)</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="compare-card row-alt">
          <div class="compare-feature">
            <div class="feature-name">Security Risk</div>
            <div class="feature-desc">How vulnerable your site is to attacks</div>
          </div>
          <div class="compare-cols">
            <div class="compare-agency">⚠️ High — WordPress is the #1 hacked platform</div>
            <div class="compare-jake">✅ Minimal — static HTML has no attack surface</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="compare-card">
          <div class="compare-feature">
            <div class="feature-name">Page Load Time</div>
            <div class="feature-desc">How fast your site loads for visitors</div>
          </div>
          <div class="compare-cols">
            <div class="compare-agency">⚠️ 5–15 seconds</div>
            <div class="compare-jake">✅ Under 1 second</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="compare-card row-alt">
          <div class="compare-feature">
            <div class="feature-name">Lighthouse Performance Score</div>
            <div class="feature-desc">Google's official website performance grade</div>
          </div>
          <div class="compare-cols">
            <div class="compare-agency">⚠️ 50–75 / 100</div>
            <div class="compare-jake">✅ 100 / 100 — Perfect</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="compare-card">
          <div class="compare-feature">
            <div class="feature-name">ADA / WCAG Accessibility</div>
            <div class="feature-desc">Legal compliance for users with disabilities</div>
          </div>
          <div class="compare-cols">
            <div class="compare-agency">⚠️ Rarely included</div>
            <div class="compare-jake">✅ Built in, every page</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="compare-card row-alt">
          <div class="compare-feature">
            <div class="feature-name">You Own the Website</div>
            <div class="feature-desc">Full code and content ownership</div>
          </div>
          <div class="compare-cols">
            <div class="compare-agency">⚠️ Sometimes held hostage</div>
            <div class="compare-jake">✅ Always — it's yours outright</div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div style="margin-top:2rem;background:#fef9c3;border:2px solid #fbbf24;border-radius:0.75rem;padding:1.25rem 1.5rem;">
        <p style="color:#92400e;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">
          💡 <strong>Quick math:</strong> If an agency is charging you $700/yr for SSL + $50/mo for hosting + $30/mo for backups, that's over <strong>$1,660 per year</strong> for things that are completely free with a modern stack. Over 5 years that's $8,300+ — on top of what you paid to build the site.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WordPress vs Astro -->
  <section style="background:#f8fafc;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:72rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">The Platform Problem</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">WordPress Was Great in 2010. It's 2026.</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;max-width:40rem;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;line-height:1.75;">WordPress powers a huge portion of the web — which is exactly why it's the number one target for hackers. It requires constant updates, plugin maintenance, and ongoing costs just to keep it running safely.</p>
      </div>
      <div id="platform-grid">
        <div class="platform-card platform-bad">
          <div class="platform-header-bad">
            <h3>WordPress</h3>
            <span class="platform-tag-bad">Old School</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="platform-list">
            <li>⚠️ #1 most hacked website platform</li>
            <li>⚠️ Requires constant plugin updates</li>
            <li>⚠️ Plugins conflict and break things</li>
            <li>⚠️ Database driven — slow by default</li>
            <li>⚠️ Needs paid hosting to run</li>
            <li>⚠️ Performance requires extra paid plugins</li>
            <li>⚠️ Accessibility requires extra paid plugins</li>
            <li>⚠️ Heavy, bloated pages by default</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="platform-card platform-good">
          <div class="platform-header-good">
            <h3>Astro + Cloudflare</h3>
            <span class="platform-tag-good">Modern Stack</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="platform-list">
            <li>✅ Static HTML — nothing to hack</li>
            <li>✅ No plugins, no updates to manage</li>
            <li>✅ Nothing to conflict or break</li>
            <li>✅ Pre-built pages — loads instantly</li>
            <li>✅ Free hosting on Cloudflare Pages</li>
            <li>✅ Performance is built in by design</li>
            <li>✅ Accessibility built in from scratch</li>
            <li>✅ Lean, fast pages under 200kb</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom Line -->
  <section style="background:white;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;text-align:center;">
      <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-bottom:1rem;">The Bottom Line</h2>
      <p style="color:#4b5563;line-height:1.85;font-size:1.05rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">
        You deserve a website that loads fast, ranks well on Google, is accessible to every visitor, and doesn't come with a monthly bill for things that are free. That's not a premium add-on — that's just what a website should be in 2026.
      </p>
      <p style="color:#4b5563;line-height:1.85;font-size:1.05rem;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        Every site I build scores 100/100 on Lighthouse Performance and 10/10 on WAVE accessibility. It's hosted for free on Cloudflare's global network, backed up automatically on GitHub, and secured with a free SSL certificate. You own it outright from day one. No recurring fees for things that should have been free all along.
      </p>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center;gap:1rem;">
        <a href="/web-services" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:#2563eb;color:white;font-weight:700;padding:0.875rem 2rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;">
          View Web Packages
          <svg style="height:1rem;width:1rem;" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/contact" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:white;color:#1e3a8a;font-weight:700;padding:0.875rem 2rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;border:2px solid #1e3a8a;">
          Get a Free Quote
          <svg style="height:1rem;width:1rem;" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  #speed-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto 3rem auto;
  }

  .speed-card {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .speed-label {
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #111827;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .speed-bar-wrap {
    background: #f3f4f6;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    height: 2.5rem;
    width: 100%;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .speed-bar {
    height: 100%;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .speed-bar-bad {
    background: #fca5a5;
    color: #7f1d1d;
  }

  .speed-bar-good {
    background: #86efac;
    color: #14532d;
    min-width: 60px;
  }

  .speed-note {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: #6b7280;
    margin: 0;
  }

  #stat-cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .stat-card {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .stat-number {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #111827;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .stat-sub {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: #6b7280;
  }

  #tools-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: stretch;
  }

  .tool-card {
    background: #f8fafc;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
